      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Only five for the Byerley - the longest 2yo race in the country. Siding with DELAHRA (4) who really caught the eye last start at Sandown Lakeside when just missing a nose. They went slowly there and ripped home but she kept coming and while quickly up in trip isn't ideal, they surely at a crawl in the small field on trial at the trip which will suit. KO PHANGAN (1) comes through the best form race, sticking on well for third in the Taj Rossi Final last time out over a mile. 1800m will be no issue and Williams will kick up from the inside gate. NOTIFIED (2) looked handy winning at Ballarat Synthetic last time despite racing wide and moving into it early. Onto turf for the first time is interesting but she should stay the trip well. ACHY BREAKY HEART (3) has a bit to find from the Taj Rossi - STUNNING KITTY (5) has a lot.",
